au.gov.naa.digipres.xena.kernel.guesser
Class GuesserManager

java.lang.Object
  au.gov.naa.digipres.xena.kernel.guesser.GuesserManager

public class GuesserManager
extends java.lang.Object

Manages instances of Guesser objects, well as the guessing of types of XenaInputSources.

Guesser objects are used to determine the 'XenaType'of a given input source. A guesser will take a XenaInputSource, create a Guess object and then check for a number of different attributes in the input source, and set flags in the Guess object accordingly. The GuesserManager will then take the returned guess, and generate a ranking for it based on the currently active GuessRanker object. The highest rank guess then wins.

On instantiation, the the guesser manager creates the binary guesser

getGuesses

public java.util.List<Guess> getGuesses(XenaInputSource xenaInputSource)
Get a list of guess objects for the supplied XenaInputSource. Do this by getting each loaded guesser to return a guess for the input source. Rank them using the GuessRanker and then sort them so that the zeroth element is the most likely guess, and the last element in the list is the least likely. Return the list.

Parameters:
xenaInputSource - - the input source to guess. This must NOT be null.
Returns:
List - A list of guesses for the given XenaInputSource

getBestGuess

public Guess getBestGuess(XenaInputSource source)
                   throws java.io.IOException
Get the best guess for the given XIS, while making as few guesses as possible. The guessers are first sorted in order of the maximum ranking that each can produce. The guessers then guess the type in turn, with guessers with the higher maximum possible ranking guessing first. The current leading guess ranking is tracked, and if this leading ranking becomes higher than the maximum possible ranking of the current guesser, then there is no point going any further as it is impossible for the current leading ranking to be beaten by any of the remaining guessers.

Parameters:
source -
Returns:
best guess, or null if no guessers available
Throws:
java.io.IOException

getBestGuess

public Guess getBestGuess(XenaInputSource source,
                          java.util.List<java.lang.String> disabledTypeList)
                   throws java.io.IOException
Get the best guess for the given XIS, while making as few guesses as possible. The guessers are first sorted in order of the maximum ranking that each can produce. The guessers then guess the type in turn, with guessers with the higher maximum possible ranking guessing first. The current leading guess ranking is tracked, and if this leading ranking becomes higher than the maximum possible ranking of the current guesser, then there is no point going any further as it is impossible for the current leading ranking to be beaten by any of the remaining guessers. The given list contains the names of types that are to be disabled, or ignored. The guessed type thus cannot be one of these types.

best guess, or null if no guessers available
